    "Introduction BackgroundMachine learning (ML) algorithms have become pervasive in today's world, influencing a wide range of fields, from governance and financial decision-making to medical diagnosis and security assessment.",
    "These technologies depend on artificial intelligence (AI) and ML to provide results, offering clear advantages in terms of speed and cost-effectiveness for businesses over time [1].",
    "However, as AI research progresses rapidly, the importance of ensuring that its development and deployment adhere to ethical principles has become paramount.User data on social media platforms (SMPs) can reveal patterns, trends, and behaviors.",
